The figure below shows a quadrilateral with two right angles.  The distance between these two right-angled vertices can be written in the form $\tfrac{a+b\sqrt c}d$, where $a$, $b$, and $d$ are relatively prime positive integers and $c$ is not divisible by the square of any prime.  What is $a+b+c+d$?
            \begin{figure}[ht]
        \centering
        \begin{asy}
        texpreamble("\usepackage{kpfonts}");
        import olympiad;
        size(125);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7));
pair A = (0,2), B = (3,0), C = origin, D = rotate(160,(A+B)/2)*C;
draw(A--C--B--D--A);
draw(rightanglemark(A,C,B,5)^^rightanglemark(A,D,B,5));
label("$20$",(A+C)/2,W);
label("$21$",(B+C)/2,S);
label("$27$",(A+D)/2,dir(80));
\end{asy}
\end{figure}
